In some European countries, internet providers are legally required to let governments insert fake files or harmful software, like trojans, into users’ downloads. This means when you download something, it might secretly carry spyware or malware without your knowledge. This practice can compromise privacy and security. Using tools that don’t rely on the internet or downloading from unknown sources helps protect your data and devices from these hidden risks. Keywords to explore include “ISP data injection,” “government malware,” and “download tampering.”